<div id="looxReviews" data-product-id="8185180618992" class="loox-reviews-default">
  <div id="loox-inline-reviews" style="display:none" data-loox-hash="1702845543773"><div class="review"><div class="name">Alice T.</div><div class="review_text">Batteries dead in less than 7 days. </div></div><div class="review"><div class="name">Alice T.</div><div class="review_text">Ordered 2 of these kits and just installed and tested already having issue with one of the smoke detectors doesn’t seem to work and another the battery is already showing very  low battery! Only had these up less than a week! </div></div><div class="review"><div class="name">Verne S.</div><div class="review_text">Have 3 buildings all tied together with one system. easy to set up, easy to mount. and they all work together with no issues. really happy with system.

verne</div></div><div class="review"><div class="name">Philip W.</div><div class="review_text">System hooked up with ease.
App was easy to navigate and set up.
Syncing of the devices to the hub was smooth,
Labeling and Mounting of the smoke detectors went quick and a quick test demonstrated that it works.
Only wish…
I wish I could add carbon ‘monoxide detection to the system.</div></div><div class="review"><div class="name">Hunter S.</div><div class="review_text">Incredibly simple to set up and install. Love the interconnected feature and the hub to monitor statuses. </div></div><div class="review"><div class="name">Daniel F.</div><div class="review_text">all the smoke detectors seamlessly connected with no issues</div></div><div class="review"><div class="name">Mitchell</div><div class="review_text">I bought the two piece set as a starter kit to see if it was easy to connect and if it really worked, and so far my experience has been very good. The packaging has detailed and easy to understand instructions on how to connect, test the connection and disconnect if needed. To activate it you simply mount it in the desired position using the mounting plate and then mount the smoke alarms on the mounting plate so that they turn on automatically. This has brought considerable extra convenience and safety to my large house.</div></div><div class="review"><div class="name">Dave</div><div class="review_text">It seems you have to test the system with a real alarm, or maybe that's the only way I can get all the units to alarm. Holding down the test button did not make all the units alarm. However, when I used canned smoke, all the units went into alarm mode and made that annoying noise.</div></div><div class="review"><div class="name">Jose Rodriguez Jr</div><div class="review_text">They are very easy to install and even easier to attach together. Just make sure you choose one as the main one. I used the one in the living room as the main control. They work well and they both make a sound when one of them detects smoke. I know because I burned dinner the other night and they both made a sound. Worth a try.</div></div></div>
</div>

