</section><div id="shopify-section-template--20537570918640__product-faqs" class="shopify-section"><div id="faq" class="product-faq mt-10 tw-container">
  <h3 class="description-title">FAQs</h3>
  <div class="classify-faq-box">
    
      <dl x-data="{ active: false }" class="classify-faq-item">
        <dt @click="active = !active" :class="{ &#39;active&#39;: active }">
          <p>Will this smoke alarm work without being paired to the base station?</p>

          <i class="icon"></i>
        </dt>
        <dd style="display: none;" x-show="active">Yes. If the alarm is disconnected from the base station, it will continue to operate as a wireless interconnected smoke alarm. You will also see "Offline" on the app's device list and receive a push notification.</dd>
      </dl>
    
      <dl x-data="{ active: false }" class="classify-faq-item">
        <dt @click="active = !active" :class="{ &#39;active&#39;: active }">
          <p>How much does the app cost?</p>

          <i class="icon"></i>
        </dt>
        <dd style="display: none;" x-show="active">Nothing yet. You will receive push notifications via the X-Sense Home Security app at no cost.</dd>
      </dl>
    
      <dl x-data="{ active: false }" class="classify-faq-item">
        <dt @click="active = !active" :class="{ &#39;active&#39;: active }">
          <p>How can I add more users to the X-Sense Home Security app for monitoring the alarms on their phones as well?</p>

          <i class="icon"></i>
        </dt>
        <dd style="display: none;" x-show="active">Go to the alarm’s Device Settings and select Device Sharing. Add your family and friends to the system by entering their X-Sense account email addresses. This way all users will receive notifications and can control the devices in their app.</dd>
      </dl>
    
      <dl x-data="{ active: false }" class="classify-faq-item">
        <dt @click="active = !active" :class="{ &#39;active&#39;: active }">
          <p>Can I add additional smoke alarms after the system is set up?</p>

          <i class="icon"></i>
        </dt>
        <dd style="display: none;" x-show="active">Yes! You can pair up to 50 smoke alarms with the same base station to give your home full protection. For more details, please refer to the user manual.</dd>
      </dl>
    
      <dl x-data="{ active: false }" class="classify-faq-item">
        <dt @click="active = !active" :class="{ &#39;active&#39;: active }">
          <p>Can it communicate with other Link⁺ series alarms?</p>

          <i class="icon"></i>
        </dt>
        <dd style="display: none;" x-show="active">The XS01-M devices can be connected to other Link⁺ series alarms without a base station, as well as through a Wi-Fi network to the base station. You can choose only one of these connection options. <br>
When connected to the SBS50 base station, the XS01-M devices communicate with each other and can be controlled through the app. If one device is triggered, all will sound an alarm. However, the XS01-M devices cannot communicate with other Link+ device models.<br>
If you want the XS01-M devices to communicate with other Link⁺ devices, please refer to the user manual and follow the instructions for connecting them. Keep in mind that doing so will disable app controls and notifications.</dd>
      </dl>
    
  </div>
</div>


